'''Eric Nshimiyimana''' (born 8 May 1972) is a Rwandan [[association football|football]] coach and former player. He currently coaches [[Rwanda National Football League]] side [[S.C. Kiyovu Sports|Kiyovu Sports]].

==Career==

===Playing career===
Born in [[Bujumbura]] in Burundi, Nshimiyimana played as a [[midfielder]] for [[Prince Louis F.C.|Prince Louis]] and [[Armée Patriotique Rwandaise F.C.|APR]].<ref name = "NFT">{{cite web |url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/5491.html |title=Player profile |website=National-Football-Teams.com |accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

He played for the [[Rwanda national football team|Rwandan national team]] between 1996 and 2004,<ref name = "NFT"/> appearing in four FIFA World Cup qualifying matches for them.<ref>{{FIFA|157517}}</ref> He was a squad member at the [[2004 African Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/3397443.stm|title=Rwanda name finals squad|date=14 January 2004|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>

===Coaching career===
Nshimiyimana became an assistant coach for the [[Rwanda national football team|Rwandan national team]] in April 2008, working [[Raoul Shungu]] to assist manager [[Branko Tucak]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/7369926.stm|title=Tucak appointed Rwanda coach|date=27 April 2008|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> When Tucak was sacked in November 2009, Nshimiyimana became interim manager of the national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/8377171.stm|title=Rwanda sack Croatian coach Tucak|date=24 November 2009|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He was re-appointed manager in 2013; in April 2014 the Rwandan Football Association announced an 8-man shortlist to replace him after his contract expired on 30 June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27158313|title=Ratomir Dujkovic on shortlist for Rwanda coach position|date=25 April 2014|accessdate=27 April 2014|author=Andrew Jackson Oryada|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> In July 2014, he became the coach of [[S.C. Kiyovu Sports|Kiyovu Sports]] ahead of the 2014–15 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201407090415.html|title=Rwanda: Nshimiyimana Named As SC Kiyovu Coach|date=8 July 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014|author=Peter Kamasa|publisher=allAfrica.com}}</ref>

